  "commentary": "With SPX at 6599.07 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-25.5B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+31.1B), dealers are likely covering short hedges and transitioning to selling pressure as spot approaches the 6605 wall. The PIN regime combined with the massive 8.4B total GEX suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push above 6605 and provide buying support if we test the 6590 level, creating a tight trading range. Watch for rejection at 6605 and support at 6590, with the 6697 flip strike acting as the broader upside ceiling where dealer behavior would reverse.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590 and 6605 with limited movement in either direction.",
